Competencies

Everything is an object, everything has it own characteristics
You can make new objects with their own properties by declaring new classes
Instances are members of a certain class and have all the attributes and methods 
Class methods vs Instance methods: class methods are called on a class, instance methods are called on the instance. Puppy.new vs fido.speak
When declaring a class, you can give it instance methods to perform within the class declaration
Special method: Initialize. Gives the class certain characteristics “right out of the box”
Class attributes are declared in the “initialize” method


Applications
Design and define new objects
Set attributes and methods for objects
